        explanation: 'When a government spends more than it collects by way of revenue, it incurs a budget deficit.\n\nPrimary deficit is simply the fiscal deficit minus the interest payments.\nPrimary Deficit (PD) = Fiscal Deficit (FD) − Interest Payments;  zero primary deficit means the\ngovernment’s current revenues are sufficient to meet its non-interest expenditure; borrowing is only\n\nto service past debt. Hence option (c) is the correct answer.',
