        explanation: 'Timur was an invader from Central Asia who invaded India in 1398 AD during the reign of\nNasiruddin MuhamImad Tughlaq. He recklessly plundered the country, thus causing brutal\nmassacrSes, looting and dishonouring women.\nNadir Shah- It was during the reign of Mohd. Saha, Rangeela/Roshan Akhtar that the Nadir\nShah (c.1739 ) invaded India. He entered Indian territory towards the end of 1738, without meeting\nwith any opposition. He attacked Delhi in March 1739. His army easily defeated the Mughals at the\n\nBattle of Karnal. The greedy invader took possession of the royal treasury and other royal property,\n\nlevied tribute on the leading nobles, and plundered the rich of Delhi. His total plunder has been\nestimated at 70 crores of rupees. He also carried away the famous Koh-i-nur diamond and the jewel-\nstudded Peacock Throne of Shahjahan. He compelled Muhammad Shah to cede to him all the\nprovinces of the Empire west of the river Indus.\nDutch East India Company -1602 (arrival in India early 17th century)\nThe Dutch established the VOC (Vereenigde Oostindische Compagnie) in 1602.\nThey focused mainly on the spice trade in Indonesia, but also established factories in India.\nMajor Dutch centers in India\nPulicat\nNagapattinam\nCochin\nThey became strong rivals of the Portuguese in the Indian Ocean.\nFrench East India Company -1664\nFounded in 1664 under the rule of Louis XIV.\n\nThe French established major settlements in India.\nImportant French settlements\nPondicherry\nChandernagore\nMahe\nKaraikal\nThe French later became major rivals of the British during the Carnatic Wars.\nHence, French arrived last among the given options.\n\nHence option (b) is the correct answer-(3-4-1-2).',
