        question: 'Consider the following statements with\nreference to Ashokan pillars:\nI. The capital of Ashokan columns shows\nHellenistic and Iranian tradition.\nII. The whole column is carved out of a\nsingle piece of buff colored sandstone\nincluding the capital.\nIII. The columns were made from sandstone,\nsourced from the quarry at Chunar.\nWhich of the statements given above is/are\ncorrect?',
