        question: 'Consider the following statements:\nStatement-I: The President of India can not\nreturn the Money Bill to the Parliament for\nreconsideration.\nStatement-II: The 24th Constitutional\nAmendment Act of 1971 made it obligatory\nfor the President to give his assent to the\nMoney Bill.\nWhich one of the following is correct in\nrespect of the above statements?',
