        question: 'As per the Constitution of India, which among\nthe following rights are enjoyed by the\nAttorney General of India?\nI. Right of audience in all courts in the\nterritory of India\nII. Right to vote in the parliamentary\nproceedings\nIII. Right to speak in the parliamentary\nproceedings\nSelect the correct answer using the code given\nbelow.',
