        question: 'Consider the following statements with respect\nto Joint sitting of the two Houses of the\nParliament:\nI. Rules for the procedure of Joint sitting of\nthe two Houses of the Parliament may be\nmade by the President of India in\nconsultation with Chairperson of Council\nof States and Speaker of the House of\nPeople.\nII. Joint sitting of two Houses shall be\npresided by the Speaker of the House of\nthe People.\nWhich among the following statements is/are\ncorrect?',
