        correct: 'b',
        explanation: 'massive bloom of Great Atlantic Sargassum Belt (GASB) across the Atlantic has raised\nconcerns.\nGreat Atlantic Sargassum Belt (GASB)\nFloating brown alga (Sargassum) stretching thousands of kilometres across Atlantic with\nsignificant human and environmental impact.\nSargassum provides food, refuge, and breeding ground for many marine animals and like other\nalgae relies on sunlight and produces oxygen during photosynthesis.\nDuring Decomposition, it consumes oxygen from water column, creating “brown tides”\nassociated with low (hypoxic) or no oxygen (anoxic) conditions.\n\nSargassum Inundation Event: First occurred in 2011 in Tropical Atlantic Ocean, outside Sargasso\nSea.\nKey Drivers: Nutrients Enrichment, Temperature (18-30°C) , Salinity, Wind and Ocean\nCirculation. Hence option (b ) is the correct answer.',
