        question: "Consider the following statements:\nStatement I: Freshwater rivers serve as a\nprimary and readily accessible source of water\nfor a substantial proportion of the global\npopulation.\nStatement II: A dominant share of the Earth's\nfreshwater reserves is present in surface water\nbodies, particularly rivers.\nWhich one of the following is correct in\nrespect of the above statements?",
        options: { a: 'Both Statement-I and Statement-II are true\nand Statement-II is the correct explanation\nof Statement-I', b: 'Both Statement-I and Statement-II are true\nbut Statement-II is not the correct\nexplanation of Statement-I', c: 'Statement-I is true but Statement-II is false', d: 'Statement-I is false but Statement-II is true' },
        correct: 'c',
        explanation: 'Freshwater rivers serve as a primary and readily accessible source of water for a substantial\nproIportion of the global population. While rivers contain only a tiny fraction of Earth\'s total water,\nthey are historically and currently the most accessible source for human settlements, agriculture,\n\nand industry.\nRivers provide water for:\nDrinking purposes\nIrrigation\nIndustrial use\nMany major civilisations (like those along the Ganga, Nile, etc.) developed around rivers.\nEven today, a large share of the global population depends on river systems and surface water for\ndaily needs. Hence, the Assertion is correct.\nThe "dominant share" of Earth\'s freshwater is actually locked in glaciers and ice caps (about 68.7%)\nand groundwater (about 30.1%). Surface water (lakes, rivers, and swamps) accounts for only about\n0.3% of all freshwater, and rivers specifically make up an even smaller fraction (approx. 0.006% of\ntotal water). Hence, the reason is not correct. Hence, option (c) is the coOrrect answer.',
        subject: 'Environment & Ecology'
