        question: 'Consider the following statements regarding\nthe International Union for Conservation of\nNature (IUCN):\nI. The IUCN World Conservation Congress\nis the world’s largest environmental\ndecision-making forum that is held every\ntwo years.\nII. It prepares legally binding international\ntreaties on wildlife conservation.\nIII. Only sovereign states can become\nmembers of the IUCN.\nWhich of the statements given above is/are\ncorrect?',
        options: { a: 'I only', b: 'II only', c: 'I and III only', d: 'None' },
        correct: 'd',
        explanation: "The IUCN World Conservation Congress is the world’s largest, most diverse environmental\ndecision-making forum, held every four years. It brings together governments, civil society,\nIndigenous peoples, and scientists to set global conservation priorities, vote on actions, and shape\npolicy for nature conservation and sustainable development. Hence, statement 1 is not correct.\nWhile the IUCN plays a significant role in nature conservation by providing expertise, compiling\nthe Red List, and influencing policy, it does not prepare legally binding international treaties itself.\nInstead, it plays a fundamental role in the drafting and implementation of conventions (such as\nCITES, Ramsar, and the World Heritage Convention), but these treaties are intergovernmental.\nHence, statement 2 is not correct.\n\nIUCN membership is not restricted to sovereign states. The IUCN is unique in that it is\ncomposed of both government and civil society organisations, including state members, government\nagencies, national and international non-governmental organisations (NGOs), and indigenous\npeoples' organisations. Hence, statement 3 is not correct.",
