        options: { a: 'Kyoto Protocol', b: 'Stockholm Convention', c: 'Nagoya Protocol', d: 'Montreal Protocol\nCopyright © by Vision IAS\nAll rights are reserved. No part of this document may be\nin any form or by any means, electronic, mechanical,\npermission of Vision IAS.' },
        correct: 'c',
        explanation: 'The NagoSya Protocol\nThe Nagoya Protocol on Access to Genetic Resources and the Fair and Equitable Sharing of\nBenefits Arising from their Utilisation to the Convention on Biological Diversity is an international\nagrIeement that aims at sharing the benefits arising from the utilisation of genetic resources in a fair\nand equitable way.\n\nAdopted in Nagoya, Japan, on 29 October 2010, it officially entered into force on 12 October 2014.\nIt covers genetic resources (plant, animal, microbial) and associated traditional knowledge (TK)\nheld by indigenous and local communities.\nThe Protocol serves to implement one of the three main goals of the Convention on Biological\nDiversity (CBD):\nFair Benefit-Sharing: Ensuring that providers (often biodiversity-rich developing countries)\nreceive a fair share of benefits when their genetic resources or associated traditional knowledge\nare used for research or commercial purposes.\nConservation Support: Encouraging that shared benefits are directed toward the conservation of\nbiological diversity and sustainable use of its components. Hence, option (c) is the correct answer.',
